<sect1 id="sect-files-openimport">
  <title>Opening Files</title>
    
  <para>
    There are several ways to open an existing file to be used in
    &gnum;. All files are opened using the <interface>Open
    File</interface> dialog. This dialog can be invoked in several
    ways. 
  </para>


  <para>
      <variablelist>
	<title>Three alternative ways to open a file</title>
        <varlistentry>
	  <term>Using the Menus</term>
	  <listitem>
	    <para> 
	      Select, in the <guimenu><accel>F</accel>ile</guimenu> menu, the
	      <guimenuitem><accel>O</accel>pen</guimenuitem> menu item.
	    </para>
	  </listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry>
	  <term>
	    Using the Standard Toolbar
	  </term>
	  <listitem>
	    <para>
	      Click on the <guibutton>Open</guibutton> button:
	      <guiicon>
		<inlinemediaobject>
            <imageobject>
              <imagedata fileref="figures/button-open.png" format="PNG" />
            </imageobject>
            <textobject>
              <phrase>An image of the open file button.</phrase>
            </textobject>
           </inlinemediaobject>
	      </guiicon>
	    </para>
	  </listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry>
	  <term>
	    Using a Keyboard Shortcut
	  </term>
	  <listitem>
	    <para>
	      Type the combintation
	      <keycombo><keysym>Ctrl</keysym><keysym>o</keysym></keycombo>,
	      typing both keys simultaneously.
	    </para>
	  </listitem>
	</varlistentry>

      </variablelist>
  </para>


  <para>
    All three methods will launch the <interface>File Open</interface>
    dialog to allow the user to find the file that they wish to open.
  </para>




